<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1170902887684">
<term>braking radiation</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1170902686692">radiation produced by targeting metal with a high-energy electron beam (or radiation produced by the acceleration of any charged particle in a material)</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1170902851307">
<term>fluorescence</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1170901867903">radiation produced by the excitation and subsequent, gradual de-excitation of an electron in an atom</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1170902772283">
<term>Moseley’s law</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1170903077586">relationship between the atomic number and X-ray photon frequency for X-ray production</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1170901478171">
<term>Moseley plot</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1170902759776">plot of the atomic number versus the square root of X-ray frequency</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1170901626575">
<term>selection rules</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1170901635157">rules that determine whether atomic transitions are allowed or forbidden (rare)</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
